    "updated_at": "2024-01-15T16:20:15Z",
    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Thanks for reporting this issue! I can reproduce the problem.\n\nThe issue is in our username validation regex in `src/auth/validation.py`. The current pattern is too restrictive:\n\n```python\n# Current (too restrictive)\nUSERNAME_PATTERN = r'^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$'\n\n# Should be (more flexible)\nUSERNAME_PATTERN = r'^[a-zA-Z0-9_.@+-]+$'\n```\n\nI'll prepare a fix for this in the authentication branch. This should be a quick fix that we can include in the v2.0.0 release.\n\n@bug-reporter Can you test with the updated pattern once I push the fix?",
